<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?>
<!--
  Anonymized derivative of a real Burlington Hydro "Download My Data" feed
  (Electricity 60-minute, ~1 week). Trimmed to 2 IntervalBlocks × 3 readings each so the
  fixture stays small while still exercising:
    * UsagePoint + ServiceCategory + status
    * MeterReading (empty content)
    * Multiple IntervalBlocks each with multiple IntervalReadings
    * ReadingType with all 12 scalar fields
    * LocalTimeParameters

  Identifiers (RetailCustomer UUID, UsagePoint UUID, MeterReading UUID, IntervalBlock UUIDs,
  hostnames) are synthetic. Reading values are rounded to the nearest 100 Wh. The XML
  structure — namespaces, element ordering, empty elements, line breaks — mirrors what the
  utility actually emits, so the parser sees the real wire shape.
-->
